### Explanation:
1. **`filter(num => num % 2 === 0)`**: This method creates a new array with all elements that pass the test implemented by the provided function. In this case, it filters out only the even numbers.
2. **`reduce((acc, num) => acc + num, 0)`**: This method reduces the array to a single value by applying a function against an accumulator and each element in the array (from left to right). The initial value of the accumulator is `0`.

This function will work with any array of numbers and will correctly sum up all the even numbers in it.
